[30;1m52 | [0m[35mIt takes the current version of[0m
[30;1m53 | [0m[35mthe source from git tags and any additional commits. For development, the version will have a[0m
[30;1m54 | [0m[35mstring like ``0.1.1+76.g136e37b.dirty``, which comes from ``git describe``. This version means[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35mthat the current code is 76 commits past the 0.1.1 tag, on git hash ``136e37b``, with local[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35mchanges on top (indicated by ``dirty``). For a release, or non-git repo source dir, the version[0m

[30;1m42 | [0m[35mand squash together smaller commits. It's not necessary to flatten the entire branch, but it[0m
[30;1m43 | [0m[35mcan be nice to eliminate small fixes and get the merge down to logically arranged commit. This[0m
[30;1m44 | [0m[35mcan also be used to hide sins from history--this is the only chance, since once it hits[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35m``main``, it's there forever![0m
